started driving faster.

256
00:11:31,674 --> 00:11:33,058
Did she say anything?

257
00:11:33,126 --> 00:11:35,109
She told us to shut up.

258
00:11:35,178 --> 00:11:36,611
She said that?

259
00:11:36,679 --> 00:11:37,862
She's never said that.

260
00:11:38,881 --> 00:11:41,182
We weren't even making noise.

261
00:11:41,251 --> 00:11:43,246
And then we started
to hit other cars,

262
00:11:43,270 --> 00:11:45,403
and then we went into the water,

263
00:11:45,471 --> 00:11:47,350
and then a fireman
pulled me out.

264
00:11:47,374 --> 00:11:49,073
God.

265
00:11:50,126 --> 00:11:52,421
You said "shut up"
was a bad word.

266
00:11:52,445 --> 00:11:53,556
You said...

267
00:11:53,580 --> 00:11:56,313
No, it's okay. You're okay.

268
00:11:56,382 --> 00:11:59,117
It's true, Parker.
You're a lucky kid.

269
00:11:59,185 --> 00:12:02,770
All you need is a little splint
on that wrist, but that's it.

270
00:12:02,839 --> 00:12:05,823
Okay. Your daughter's
still just a little groggy.

271
00:12:05,892 --> 00:12:07,903
Just need to stitch up
that laceration on her face.

272
00:12:07,927 --> 00:12:09,638
- She's good to go.
- Yes. Of course.

273
00:12:09,662 --> 00:12:11,374
Please, do whatever
you have to do.

274
00:12:11,398 --> 00:12:12,714
Dr. Avery, a word?

275
00:12:13,733 --> 00:12:14,832
Uh, excuse me.

276
00:12:14,901 --> 00:12:16,384
One second. Uh-huh.

277
00:12:21,057 --> 00:12:22,390
Hey. You all right?

278
00:12:22,458 --> 00:12:24,087
I'll get somebody to cover
for me, and we can just go...

279
00:12:24,111 --> 00:12:25,543
What is wrong with you?

280
00:12:25,612 --> 00:12:27,656
Letting a cop interrogate
a five-year-old?

281
00:12:27,680 --> 00:12:28,913
They needed to know...

282
00:12:28,982 --> 00:12:31,632
Those kids were almost
killed by their mother.

283
00:12:31,701 --> 00:12:33,112
They're terrified.

284
00:12:33,136 --> 00:12:34,746
Okay. Slow down.
They're in shock.

285
00:12:34,770 --> 00:12:36,449
Listen, listen, I think
you're in shock, actually.

286
00:12:36,473 --> 00:12:38,150
They shouldn't even be down
here. Get them out of here.

287
00:12:38,174 --> 00:12:40,069
Get them someplace
safe. Get them admitted.

288
00:12:40,093 --> 00:12:41,542
Okay. Let's just go home.

289
00:12:41,628 --> 00:12:43,794
Have you seen
those people in there?

290
00:12:43,863 --> 00:12:45,195
What that woman did?

291
00:12:45,265 --> 00:12:46,743
I know, and there are
plenty of people here

292
00:12:46,767 --> 00:12:47,977
that can take
care of them, right?

293
00:12:48,001 --> 00:12:50,084
You need to...

294
00:12:50,153 --> 00:12:52,233
I... I need to be in an OR.

295
00:12:52,272 --> 00:12:55,051
But you seem to be making all
sorts of decisions for me today.

296
00:12:55,075 --> 00:12:56,173
I'm trying to help you.

297
00:12:56,242 --> 00:12:57,642
Yeah, you're not helping.

298
00:12:57,710 --> 00:12:59,455
You go to Owen, and
then two men decide

299
00:12:59,479 --> 00:13:00,873
what they think is
best for the little lady,

300
00:13:00,897 --> 00:13:02,841
like I'm some helpless idiot,

301
00:13:02,865 --> 00:13:04,544
and then I suddenly find myself
standing outside of my OR?

302
00:13:04,568 --> 00:13:06,601
That is not helping!

303
00:13:06,670 --> 00:13:08,169
Why don't you tell
me what is, then?

304
00:13:08,238 --> 00:13:09,870
Talk to me instead
of running away.

305
00:13:09,939 --> 00:13:12,659
Tell me what you need. Tell me
what I can do. Tell me how you feel.

306
00:13:12,709 --> 00:13:15,709
Tell me something, anything.
Say something. Talk to me.

307
00:13:15,796 --> 00:13:17,706
I'm trying to help you.
That's all I'm trying to do here.

308
00:13:17,730 --> 00:13:20,192
Okay, okay. You
want to help? Yes.

309
00:13:20,216 --> 00:13:21,761
Just get that family into a room

310
00:13:21,785 --> 00:13:24,025
and stitch up that girl's face.

311
00:13:46,175 --> 00:13:48,759
Everything okay?

312
00:14:12,585 --> 00:14:13,651
No.

313
00:14:17,574 --> 00:14:20,208
Everything is not okay.

314
00:14:26,599 --> 00:14:28,499
We need your parents' names.

315
00:14:28,567 --> 00:14:31,002
They need to know that
you're here and you're safe.

316
00:14:31,070 --> 00:14:32,669
Just cough it up.

317
00:14:32,738 --> 00:14:35,606
You don't say a word.
You're a brick wall.

318
00:14:35,674 --> 00:14:37,687
Dylan's CT shows
mesenteric stranding

319
00:14:37,711 --> 00:14:39,438
and some thickening
of the bowel wall.

320
00:14:39,462 --> 00:14:41,346
Could be just a
mesenteric injury,

321
00:14:41,414 --> 00:14:43,208
but it also looks like
a bucket-handle injury.

322
00:14:43,232 --> 00:14:45,794
I'll just go in and take a look
first with the laparoscope.

323
00:14:45,818 --> 00:14:46,818
Uh-uh.

324
00:14:47,687 --> 00:14:49,019
No. Come here.

325
00:14:51,991 --> 00:14:53,358
No, we need to get in there,

326
00:14:53,426 --> 00:14:55,170
open him up and
see what's happening.

327
00:14:55,194 --> 00:14:56,661
Laparoscopic isn't the standard.

328
00:14:56,730 --> 00:14:58,095
You could miss a bowel perf.

329
00:14:58,164 --> 00:14:59,442
But I'm trying to save this kid

330
00:14:59,466 --> 00:15:00,676
a massive scar
and a long recovery.

331
00:15:00,700 --> 00:15:01,927
Yeah, but we shouldn't risk...

332
00:15:01,951 --> 00:15:03,384
Why do you keep saying "we"?

333
00:15:03,453 --> 00:15:05,293
You're not doing
it at all. He's a kid.

334
00:15:05,338 --> 00:15:07,015
You don't tell me what
I'm doing and not...

335
00:15:07,039 --> 00:15:08,189
You're a kid.

336
00:15:08,257 --> 00:15:10,819
I'm an attending pediatric
surgeon, and he's a kid.

337
00:15:10,843 --> 00:15:11,870
It's my call,

338
00:15:11,894 --> 00:15:14,175
and I'm going in
laparoscopically.

339
00:15:14,281 --> 00:15:15,646
Oh.

340
00:15:15,715 --> 00:15:17,081
Is that how it's gonna be?

341
00:15:17,150 --> 00:15:18,432
Yeah. It is.

342
00:15:18,501 --> 00:15:19,645
And maybe while I do that,

343
00:15:19,669 --> 00:15:20,879
you can get his
little rat brother

344
00:15:20,903 --> 00:15:23,621
to roll over on his
parents. Okay?

345
00:15:26,176 --> 00:15:28,208
Let's get him ready to roll.

346
00:15:28,277 --> 00:15:29,517
You're a brick wall, Jack.

347
00:15:29,579 --> 00:15:30,745
Brick it!

348
00:15:35,685 --> 00:15:39,053
Okay, that should
prevent any tamponading.

349
00:15:40,623 --> 00:15:44,025
One woman loses it, and look
at all the damage she can do.

350
00:15:44,093 --> 00:15:46,672
There's a chest contusion with
intermittent arrhythmias in bed six.

351
00:15:46,696 --> 00:15:49,697
Can you take a look at
that next? Mmm-hmm.

352
00:15:49,766 --> 00:15:51,398
Boy or girl? What?

353
00:15:52,485 --> 00:15:54,585
Oh, are you guys
not finding out?

354
00:15:54,653 --> 00:15:55,786
I am such a control freak.

355
00:15:55,855 --> 00:15:58,122
I don't think I could
handle not knowing.

356
00:15:58,191 --> 00:16:01,292
I would want to have
a list of names in mind.

357
00:16:01,361 --> 00:16:04,628
That would be the hardest
part, I think, choosing the name.

358
00:16:04,697 --> 00:16:08,132
Bed six, consult. Now, please.

359
00:16:08,201 --> 00:16:10,017
Okay.

360
00:16:10,086 --> 00:16:12,836
Uh, I'm looking for Greg
James. Is he still down here?

361
00:16:12,905 --> 00:16:14,405
I need to talk to you.

362
00:16:15,475 --> 00:16:16,986
Okay. So, you talked to Jackson.

363
00:16:17,010 --> 00:16:18,921
Are you okay? Can I do anything?

364
00:16:18,945 --> 00:16:22,113
You saw something
on my ultrasound.

365
00:16:22,182 --> 00:16:23,448
Yes.

366
00:16:23,516 --> 00:16:26,451
Yes, you saw something,
and you didn't say anything.

367
00:16:26,519 --> 00:16:28,319
I know. I...

368
00:16:28,388 --> 00:16:30,088
I was right there in the room.

369
00:16:30,156 --> 00:16:33,257
It was my baby,
and you said nothing.

370
00:16:33,326 --> 00:16:34,692
Nothing.

371
00:16:34,760 --> 00:16:36,738
I just wanted to be
sure before I told you.

372
00:16:36,762 --> 00:16:39,058
Oh, but you had no problem
going and telling other people.

373
00:16:39,082 --> 00:16:41,482
You had no problem
telling Jackson

374
00:16:41,550 --> 00:16:45,219
before I even had a
chance to process. I'm sorry.

375
00:16:45,287 --> 00:16:48,255
To have you, of all people,
knowing before I did.

376
00:16:51,828 --> 00:16:52,893
I'm sorry.

377
00:16:52,962 --> 00:16:54,478
Yeah, you should be.

378
00:16:59,018 --> 00:17:01,485
Mr. James is upstairs.
His kids were admitted.

379
00:17:07,910 --> 00:17:09,176
Hello. This is OR one.

380
00:17:09,245 --> 00:17:11,456
Did he tell Amelia? Did
he pass off his cases?

381
00:17:11,480 --> 00:17:14,682
I'm sure he did. Derek
wouldn't just leave his patients.

382
00:17:14,751 --> 00:17:16,450
Pickups.

383
00:17:16,519 --> 00:17:18,619
Or his wife or his kids.

384
00:17:18,688 --> 00:17:20,855
It's just hard to believe.

385
00:17:20,923 --> 00:17:22,005
He did.

386
00:17:22,075 --> 00:17:24,909
And what do you need?
Someone to blame?

387
00:17:24,977 --> 00:17:27,745
It's my fault. I did
it. I told him to go.

388
00:17:28,581 --> 00:17:29,963
Stapler.

389
00:17:30,050 --> 00:17:31,877
Dr. Grey, her tox screen's back.

390
00:17:31,901 --> 00:17:34,568
Any drugs or alcohol?
Antipsychotics? Antidepressants?

391
00:17:34,637 --> 00:17:36,687
All negative. Damn it!

392
00:17:36,756 --> 00:17:37,833
What are you after?

393
00:17:37,857 --> 00:17:39,674
An explanation. Something.

394
00:17:39,742 --> 00:17:41,382
Someone puts her
whole family in danger,

395
00:17:41,444 --> 00:17:43,577
you want to find out
there was a good reason.

396
00:17:45,398 --> 00:17:48,282
You want to believe she
didn't have any choice.

397
00:17:52,188 --> 00:17:53,632
Have you talked to Cristina?

398
00:17:53,656 --> 00:17:56,986
I presume you guys talk
all the time, especially now.

399
00:17:57,010 --> 00:17:59,510
Yeah, we usually get on the
phone Friday nights for me,

400
00:17:59,578 --> 00:18:02,429
Saturday mornings for
her, pour drinks, settle in.

401
00:18:02,498 --> 00:18:04,899
So, today's Friday. You
gonna call her today?

402
00:18:06,002 --> 00:18:09,103
Yeah, I've missed
the last couple.

403
00:18:09,872 --> 00:18:11,689
Why?

404
00:18:11,757 --> 00:18:13,803
Before she left, she said
something about Derek and I,

405
00:18:13,827 --> 00:18:16,327
and she was right.

406
00:18:17,530 --> 00:18:19,597
And I don't want
her to be right.

407
00:18:20,667 --> 00:18:23,317
Hmm. Hmm.

408
00:18:23,386 --> 00:18:27,838
Okay, so, no history
of diabetes in the family.

409
00:18:27,907 --> 00:18:31,142
What about, uh, current
illnesses or mental illnesses?

410
00:18:31,210 --> 00:18:33,188
Are you asking if
my wife's crazy?

411
00:18:33,212 --> 00:18:35,212
No, we're trying to
see if there's something

412
00:18:35,281 --> 00:18:36,613
that could have made her do...

413
00:18:36,682 --> 00:18:39,449
To hurt my kids?
Nothing. She wouldn't.

414
00:18:43,222 --> 00:18:44,755
I didn't think she would.

415
00:18:47,193 --> 00:18:49,893
Brooke. I mean, she's, uh...

416
00:18:51,264 --> 00:18:53,030
She's busy.

417
00:18:53,099 --> 00:18:55,799
You know, she's
tired and stressed.

418
00:18:56,769 --> 00:18:58,452
And she forgets things.

419
00:19:00,023 --> 00:19:01,889
She's got a lot going on

420
00:19:01,958 --> 00:19:07,061
with getting them from
school and violin and baseball.

421
00:19:08,932 --> 00:19:11,372
And making sure they're happy.

422
00:19:12,101 --> 00:19:13,400
And I...

423
00:19:14,169 --> 00:19:15,836
I work too much.

424
00:19:15,904 --> 00:19:17,338
I don't know.

425
00:19:17,940 --> 00:19:19,106
I...

426
00:19:20,476 --> 00:19:23,009
I don't know my wife.

427
00:19:26,815 --> 00:19:29,182
I don't know anything anymore.

428
00:19:33,939 --> 00:19:35,384
I left you alone
for a few minutes.

429
00:19:35,408 --> 00:19:37,708
Am I gonna find my
wallet in your pocket?

430
00:19:37,776 --> 00:19:39,554
I'm sorry that I went
behind your back.

431
00:19:39,578 --> 00:19:40,811
You're understating it.

432
00:19:40,880 --> 00:19:43,113
You betrayed me. I
thought I could trust you.

433
00:19:43,182 --> 00:19:45,760
Shepherd is fully convinced that
she can do a complete resection.

434
00:19:45,784 --> 00:19:48,886
She's convinced...
Shepherd is in a party of one.

435
00:19:48,955 --> 00:19:51,071
If there's even the
slightest bit of hope,

436
00:19:51,140 --> 00:19:52,617
don't you want to know that?

437
00:19:52,641 --> 00:19:54,925
Robbins, can you
name the single worst,

438
00:19:54,994 --> 00:19:57,828
most malignant symptom
of terminal cancer?

439
00:19:57,897 --> 00:19:59,296
It's hope.

440
00:19:59,365 --> 00:20:01,566
It's recurrent, and it
keeps creeping back in,

441
00:20:01,634 --> 00:20:04,401
no matter how many
times it gets ripped apart.

442
00:20:04,470 --> 00:20:08,121
Mayo gave me hope in a
phase three clinical trial. It failed.

443
00:20:08,208 --> 00:20:12,376
NYU hoped that radiosurgery
would work. It didn't.

444
00:20:12,445 --> 00:20:14,461
And Barrow had high, high hopes

445
00:20:14,547 --> 00:20:17,181
for a potent combination
of chemo and ablation.

446
00:20:17,250 --> 00:20:18,349
No go.

447
00:20:18,417 --> 00:20:19,916
And every time the hope goes,

448
00:20:19,985 --> 00:20:22,152
it takes chunks of you with it,

449
00:20:22,222 --> 00:20:23,688
until you can only find comfort

450
00:20:23,756 --> 00:20:27,791
in the one thing that you
know you can count on.

451
00:20:27,860 --> 00:20:29,760
That this thing
is gonna kill you.

452
00:20:31,264 --> 00:20:33,697
So you tell Shepherd to
keep her hope to herself.

453
00:20:33,766 --> 00:20:36,566
Better yet, tell her
where to stick it.

454
00:20:44,343 --> 00:20:46,560
Okay. Let's start
the anastomoses.

455
00:20:46,629 --> 00:20:48,462
Yep. 4-0 Prolene.

456
00:20:48,531 --> 00:20:50,108
Husband says there's
no history of diabetes.

457
00:20:50,132 --> 00:20:51,493
Anything else? Uh, yeah.

458
00:20:51,517 --> 00:20:53,262
She's been exhausted,
forgetful, stressed,

459
00:20:53,286 --> 00:20:54,730
running around,
taking care of the kids,

460
00:20:54,754 --> 00:20:56,031
I don't know. Maybe she snapped.

461
00:20:56,055 --> 00:20:57,771
Running around
taking care of her kids

462
00:20:57,840 --> 00:21:00,374
doesn't sound like a mom
who's about to kill herself,

463
00:21:00,442 --> 00:21:01,709
in my experience.

464
00:21:01,778 --> 00:21:03,388
Hmm. It doesn't make sense.

465
00:21:03,412 --> 00:21:05,946
Her blood-sugar levels were
so low when she came in.

466
00:21:06,015 --> 00:21:07,447
My mother always used to say,

467
00:21:07,516 --> 00:21:09,800
"The pancreas is the
self-destruct button of the body."

468
00:21:09,868 --> 00:21:12,081
And her pancreas
was really friable.

469
00:21:12,105 --> 00:21:14,287
And her husband said
she's been forgetful.

470
00:21:15,858 --> 00:21:17,875
I bet there's a tumor
on that pancreas.

471
00:21:17,944 --> 00:21:19,576
Insulinoma.

472
00:21:19,645 --> 00:21:21,089
That would explain her anxiety,

473
00:21:21,113 --> 00:21:22,591
confusion, erratic behavior.

474
00:21:22,615 --> 00:21:24,081
That would explain everything.

475
00:21:24,149 --> 00:21:25,549
Yeah.

476
00:21:31,774 --> 00:21:33,351
I need to call
your parents, Jack.

477
00:21:36,029 --> 00:21:37,229
Look, you're scared.

478
00:21:37,263 --> 00:21:39,830
You think you're in trouble now.

479
00:21:39,899 --> 00:21:43,379
But believe me, the longer
you wait, the worse it'll be.

480
00:21:47,807 --> 00:21:50,641
Your parents are
scared right now,

481
00:21:50,710 --> 00:21:52,543
wondering where you are.

482
00:21:52,611 --> 00:21:56,213
And they're getting more
and more scared by the minute.

483
00:21:56,282 --> 00:21:59,150
When they finally see
you, they'll be so relieved.

484
00:22:02,288 --> 00:22:04,021
But...

485
00:22:04,090 --> 00:22:07,858
I mean, all that fear has
got to go somewhere.

486
00:22:07,927 --> 00:22:14,415
All that fear will turn
into white-hot anger

487
00:22:14,500 --> 00:22:18,935
that will banish you to a world
with no video games forever.

488
00:22:19,005 --> 00:22:21,889
Trust me. I have
a little boy, too.

489
00:22:21,958 --> 00:22:24,024
I'm a brick wall.

490
00:22:27,213 --> 00:22:28,453
Give me your cell phone.

491
00:22:28,481 --> 00:22:30,147
I'm seven.

492
00:22:30,216 --> 00:22:32,866
Would you give your
seven-year-old a cell phone?

493
00:22:32,935 --> 00:22:35,164
Look, I am trying to help you.

494
00:22:35,188 --> 00:22:37,288
If you don't cooperate,

495
00:22:37,356 --> 00:22:41,224
then I'll have to call
Child Protective Services.

496
00:22:41,293 --> 00:22:43,493
Do you know what that means?

497
00:22:49,551 --> 00:22:51,986
Hey, you want to
do this the hard way?

498
00:22:53,456 --> 00:22:55,776
Then I will make that call.

499
00:22:56,425 --> 00:22:59,259
You do what you've got to do.

500
00:23:02,382 --> 00:23:05,249
I stole a car once,
when I was 12.

501
00:23:05,317 --> 00:23:07,229
Didn't make it two blocks.

502
00:23:07,253 --> 00:23:08,386
What stopped you?

503
00:23:08,454 --> 00:23:09,753
A dumpster.

504
00:23:09,822 --> 00:23:12,456
Mmm. First time I stole a
car, I sideswiped the mirror.

505
00:23:12,524 --> 00:23:13,735
First time?

506
00:23:13,759 --> 00:23:15,258
Second time, I ran out of gas.

507
00:23:15,327 --> 00:23:17,327
Third, I got away with it.

508
00:23:17,396 --> 00:23:18,790
Fourth... Fourth?

509
00:23:18,814 --> 00:23:19,858
Flat tire.

510
00:23:19,882 --> 00:23:21,827
Are you messing with me? No.

511
00:23:21,851 --> 00:23:22,950
Was there a fifth?

