00:38:55,150 --> 00:38:56,390
Whatever you need,

802
00:38:58,920 --> 00:39:00,236
I'm here.

803
00:39:04,059 --> 00:39:06,358
Did I tell you that it's a boy?

804
00:39:08,613 --> 00:39:10,963
We're having a boy.

805
00:39:13,401 --> 00:39:15,168
<i>When shock wears off,</i>

806
00:39:18,773 --> 00:39:21,874
<i>when the body can accept
that a trauma has happened,</i>

807
00:39:26,614 --> 00:39:28,681
<i>when it can let
down its defenses...</i>

808
00:39:35,040 --> 00:39:36,322
Are you there?

809
00:39:36,391 --> 00:39:37,623
Uh, no. I'm about to, um...

810
00:39:39,594 --> 00:39:40,827
Meredith?

811
00:39:40,896 --> 00:39:43,747
I don't want to fight anymore.

812
00:39:45,250 --> 00:39:46,716
I don't, either.

813
00:39:46,784 --> 00:39:48,384
<i>And I don't want you gone.</i>

814
00:39:48,453 --> 00:39:50,720
I know that I told
you to go, but...

815
00:39:51,756 --> 00:39:54,524
I mean, this isn't us.

816
00:39:54,593 --> 00:39:56,659
This isn't how we end, is it?

817
00:39:58,230 --> 00:40:00,547
I don't want it to. I'm trying.

818
00:40:01,916 --> 00:40:03,198
I'm trying, too.

819
00:40:04,535 --> 00:40:06,702
Listen, my flight's
been delayed all day.

820
00:40:06,772 --> 00:40:08,605
I'm still at the airport.
I can come home.

821
00:40:09,791 --> 00:40:11,471
<i>It's a scary moment.</i>

822
00:40:12,910 --> 00:40:14,193
Do I come home?

823
00:40:16,131 --> 00:40:17,897
What do we want to
promise each other?

824
00:40:17,966 --> 00:40:21,500
That you'll love me,
even when you hate me.

825
00:40:22,770 --> 00:40:26,339
To love each other even
when we hate each other.

826
00:40:26,408 --> 00:40:27,518
<i>It's vulnerable.</i>

827
00:40:27,542 --> 00:40:29,525
No. No, go.

828
00:40:29,594 --> 00:40:31,427
Meredith.

829
00:40:31,496 --> 00:40:33,262
<i>You know, in a good way. Go.</i>

